HEADWORD: Rectifier
<hw>Rec"ti*fi`er</hw> <pr>(r?k"t?*f?`?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who, or that which, rectifies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> An
instrument used for determining and rectifying the variations of the
compass on board ship. <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> A
rectificator.</def><-- (Elec.) A device to convert alternating current
to direct current. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rectify</ent>⟦br⟧
